    "description": "Join the T.I.M.E. family as a Senior Teacher in Gurgaon. We believe in empowering our employees with the tools, training, and environment they need to succeed.\n\nAbout T.I.M.E.:\nT.I.M.E. is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Maintain student records and prepare progress reports\n• Design formative and summative assessments aligned to learning objectives\n• Develop and deliver engaging lesson plans for students\n• Participate in school events, workshops, and training programs\n• Conduct parent-teacher meetings and update parents on student performance\n• Maintain classroom discipline and create a positive learning environment\n• Create curriculum-aligned learning materials and assessments\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• MBA from a recognized university\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in LMS Platforms\n• Proficiency in Data Analysis\n• Proficiency in Pedagogy\n• Proficiency in Curriculum Development\n• Proficiency in Bloom's Taxonomy\n• Proficiency in Research Skills\n• Proficiency in Educational Technology\n• Proficiency in Child Psychology\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Gurgaon, Haryana, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with T.I.M.E.!",
